@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Amiga Information Online"

@{fg shine} Welcome@{fg text}

 As another month rolls by there is no news of any developments in the
Amiga world, as we all wait in suspence until a new machine or at least
the new OS is released, but as always were back again to cheer you up
and let you in on what is good and what is not.

 This month sees more changes in the layout of AIO (again) don't worry
though there all for the better. The difference is the menus are a bit 
different to make it easier to read and navigate, thanks to Cryton for 
pointing that out!

 This month we've pulled of the stunts as usual and got and EXCLUSIVE
interview with Sadeness Software :) so check out the articles section!

 As usual remember, if you havn't filled out 'Form.txt' included with
this archive then fill it in now and get it sent off, it all goes
towards making AIO better and keeping you in touch with when new 
issues are released. Well see you same place next month, ByeeEEEeee!

 NOTE: Look out for next months issue for an exclusive interview with
Vulcan Software!

