@node "int" "Exclusive interview"

@{fg shine} Interview with Sadeness Software@{fg text}

 Yes, we've pulled it off again another Exclusive interview, this
time with exsiting publishers of onEscapee and Foundation, Sadeness
Software. Look out next month for an interview with Vulcan Software

@{b}CS:@{ub} - Chris Seward (Editor of AIO)
@{b}SS:@{ub} - Sadeness Software

CS : Please can you tell me a little about SAdENESS software and how it
     was started and set-up?

SS : We started about 4/5 years ago by starting an AGA user group,
     swapping and selling Public Domain software.  From there, we went
     on to specify in selling general public domain software.
     We worked on the AGA Experience Vol 1 CDROM for over 1 year.  Things
     went on from there.  We had a lot of help from PD Soft and Active
     Software.

CS : You have signed Foundation and OnEscapee, are you planning to stop
     there or will you be signing more games/utils?

SS : Yes, we will be trying to sign more games in the future, but at the
     moment we are happy with the 2 games which we have signed and have
     very high hopes for them.

CS : Can you tell me a little about Foundation, it's features, price
     and when it is expected to be released?

SS : By looking at the screenshots, you would instantly think, Settlers,
     but you would be wrong.  It's a mixture of Settlers, C&C, Warcraft
     and Mega Lo Mania.  It has all the elements of Settlers, fighting
     elements of Warcraft, control methods of C&C, inventory elements of
     Mega lo Mania and lots of other new features such as sea trading,
     hot air balloons for arial attacks etc.
     The release date will hopefully be before christmas, it will retail
     at 29.95 gbp

CS : Can you tell me a little about OnEscapee, it's features, price
     and when it is expected to be released?

SS : onEscapee is a mixture of Another World and Flashback, bigger
     graphics, more effects, loads of action and logic puzzles.
     Again, this will be retailed at 29.95 gbp and will be released late
     November, early December.

CS : If a programmer that is reading this issue of AIO has a game they
     think you may be interested in releasing can they contact you and
     how would they go about doing so?

SS : Sure, but it would need to be good :)  We have had people send us
     PD/Shareware games, which are basically a waste of their time and
     ours.  We are after top quality products not quantity.
     What they would need to do is either send demos via email or snail
     mail. Once we have evaluated it, we will go on from there.

CS : If any, what other games have you signed?

SS : None, so far, we have been in negotiations with a couple of other
     developers, but nothing as yet has been finalised.

CS : Can we expect to see demos of OnEscapee and Foundation soon and
     how will they be released?

SS : Indeed, there is infact a demo of onEscapee available on the Aminet,
     but a 50meg demo will be released soon on all magazine CDROMs.

CS : Releasing OnEscapee and Foundation has gained you big press but
     what other products do you sell for people who don't know?

SS : We have released our own products, which include the AGA Experience
     Vol 1, 2 and 3, the Hidden Truth and Utilities Experience which have
     all received great reviews and awards.  We also distribute other
     CDROM games and Public Domain CDROMs.

CS : What do you think of the current Amiga situation and can you
     continue to be profitable on the Amiga platform?

SS : At the moment things aren't too good, the interest in our latest
     games has been good but until they are released we just have to bite
     our lip.

CS : Would you consider a conversion of Foundation or OnEscapee to the
     PC or consoles?

SS : There is a PC conversion of onEscapee in production, and there should
     be a conversion of Foundation started soon, but that has to be
     converted into C first.

CS : What specs would you like to see in a future Amiga OS and future
     Amigas?

SS : I would like an updated workbench, more like Opus.  The new Amigas,
     I hope will come with a better graphics chip than AGA, graphics cards
     would be nice as standard.  It would be nice to see PPC and 3D chip.
     Unless the the new Amigas comes with at least PPC, hard drive,
     graphics card, 10meg and CDROM Drive as standard, then there will
     not be much hope for the future of Amiga.

CS : Thanks for your time!

SS : No problem.

