@node "fe4" "Domination Web Page" 

@{fg shine} Domination - A Game in the Making@{fg text}

@{b}The Domination homepage@{ub}

Domination is the exciting new game currently in development by 
Rammasters. The game was first invented by Mark Thomas in Summer '96. 
The game is still being worked upon now.

@{b}Our Hopes for Domination@{ub}

Domination is a space command game set in the 23rd Century. You command
various fleets of ships with which to build up your command of the
galaxy. You will be stopped in your tracks by various life forms of such
have never been encountered before by the human race. There is no set 
mission. You have the choice of playing against another player (serial 
link) or on your own, either to build up your forces for the two player 
game or just to reach a set target (making a lot of money, wiping the
galaxy clean of alien races or just to boldy go where no-one has gone 
before! :). The two player mode is the best way to fully appreciate 
Domination. You cannot see your opponent's fleets or command ships 
unless you actually find them or s/he announces them to you (sub-space 
transmission). You can wage war, set up trade routes or even form an
alliance (possibly to explore the galaxy together).

With over 200 possible events, including the invention of new, prototype
ships and improvements in existing technology, Domination grows as you
progress. You can even control the development of these technologies as
you divert funding into different areas of research.

@{b}Gaming Features@{ub}

A Workbench-like user interface, employing draggable screens for each of
the many functions, and easy-to-use iconic displays makes Domination a 
dream to play. Up to 96 different ships in twelve different classes, as 
well as space stations and command ships allow.

@{b}System Requirements@{ub}

The completed version is aimed to work on any 2MB Amiga (there may be
complications on the original A500). A fast computer would product 
smoother movements of objects in the game but it is not compulsory. A 
Hard Disk is recommended.

@{b}Progress@{ub}

While most of the game mechanism has been completed, must of the data is
still waiting to be input, and several screens are to be completed. Many
of the events have to be coded and the whole shebang has to be tested. 
There are currently over 6,400 lines of coding, and we're less than 50% 
through!

[Progress Bar (46%)]

@{b}Created using AmosPro@{ub}

However, this means that we need the AmosPro compiler. If anyone can 
compile it for us (you'll get a free copy of the game!) then e-mail or
write to us at the address below.

@{b}Want To Lend A Hand?@{ub}

We need some help with the creation of Domination. For more details,
email us.

For more details, watch this space!

To comment, send your e-mails to: dom@amiga1.demon.co.uk

------------------------------------------------------------------------

PREDICTED COMPLETION DATE

CHRISTMAS 1998

Please note, this is only a guess, and will probably change.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}The Domination "DONE" List@{ub}

(ahem)

What we have completed:

   o Design of main interface style
   o Icon bar design
   o Geological and Climatic Data, System Data, Military Actions,
     Military Catalogue, Fleet Control, Fleet Command, Mining, and 
     Options screen designed and implemented.
   o Events control mechanism
   o Two of the events (out of over 200(!), but 1% isn't that bad... :)
   o 20 out of 96 Ships Designed
   o Planet control mechanism
   o Map control
   o 2 out of 20 star systems input (Sol and Proxima)
   o 6455 lines of coding
   o plus anything else we've forgotten...

Now, see what's left to do...

@{b}The Domination "TO DO" List@{ub}

This is depressing...

